{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_3","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,260p' .claude/plans/active-codex-managed-agent-roadmap.md\"","aggregated_output":"# Active Plan — Codex-Managed-Agent Roadmap Execution\n\nPlan anchor: `ROADMAP.md`\nWorkspace: `/home/clashuser/export/codex-managed-agent`\nMirror workspace: `/home/clashuser/hzh/work_bo/codex_manager/vscode-extension`\n\n## Mission\nExecute `ROADMAP.md` to completion through bounded codex-loop slices. Do not branch into unrelated ideas. After each slice, preserve stability, package the extension, sync the dev mirror, and record a new evolution note.\n\n## Milestone Status\n\n### Milestone 1 — Architecture Stabilization\nStatus: mostly complete\n\nCompleted:\n- thin `extension.js`\n- `src/panel.js` reduced toward orchestration\n- host modules split into `server`, `codex-link`, `commands`, `auto-continue`, `lifecycle`, `panel-view`, `state-sync`\n- webview template split into `board`, `insights`, `drawer`\n\nRemaining cleanup:\n- keep `panel.js` from regrowing\n- prefer new host/webview modules for future work\n\n### Milestone 2 — Board Interaction Quality\nStatus: active\n\nTargets:\n- improve drag smoothness and drop reliability\n- finish resize behavior for all supported directions\n- define clear card-size semantics for `T / S / M / L`\n- keep `Needs Human` useful without blocking the board\n- ensure the board remains the single interactive layout surface\n\nCurrent bounded slice:\n- tighten board interaction stability by auditing drag/resizing code paths, reducing failure cases, and documenting stable card-density rules\n\n### Milestone 3 — Insight and Guidance Layer\nStatus: pending\n\nTargets:\n- stabilize usage report generation\n- improve topic map / word cloud / weekly shift interaction\n- make guidance more actionable and durable\n\n### Milestone 4 — Operational Reliability\nStatus: pending\n\nTargets:\n- background continue observability\n- clear loop status semantics\n- degraded-state handling\n- linked-vs-running distinction across surfaces\n\n### Milestone 5 — Publishable Product Quality\nStatus: pending\n\nTargets:\n- release workflow\n- screenshots / notes / docs\n- smoke validation routine\n- repo structure clarity\n\n## Slice Rules\n- Each tick completes one bounded, verifiable slice only.\n- Always validate syntax and package builds after code changes.\n- Always sync export repo changes back to the mirror workspace when behavior changes.\n- Always append an evolution note in `.claude/plans/loloop/`.\n- Update this active plan when milestone focus changes.\n\n## Immediate Next Slice Queue\n1. Board drag / resize reliability audit and fix pass\n2. T / S / M / L density normalization pass\n3. Needs Human occupancy and collapse behavior pass\n4. Board interaction polish and guardrails pass\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
